  "number": 747,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/747",
  "title": "BEM Mixins for element and modifier are inverted",
  "body": "Hi guys,\n\nIt seems that the [Sass BEM](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blame/master/src/css/_base.scss#L7-L17) mixin is using the wrong BEM convention for the `element` and `modifier` mixin:\n\n``` sass\n@mixin element($element) {\n  &--#{$element} {\n    @content\n  }\n}\n\n@mixin modifier($modifier) {\n  &__#{$modifier} {\n    @content\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAccording to [BEM](http://getbem.com/naming/) it should rather be:\n\n``` sass\n@mixin element($element) {\n  &__#{$element} {\n    @content\n  }\n}\n\n@mixin modifier($modifier) {\n  &--#{$modifier} {\n    @content\n  }\n}\n```\n",
  "created_at": "2015-12-17T16:28:13Z",
